## Step‑by‑Step Starter Guide (Shopify Example)

### 1. Store Creation
- Sign up at shopify.com → choose store name (e.g., `aiva-global.myshopify.com`).
- Select plan (Basic Shopify $29/mo) – enables credit card processing.

### 2. Basic Settings
- **Settings → Payments**: Activate Shopify Payments (supports Visa/MC/Amex) + PayPal.
- **Settings → Checkout**: Enable customer accounts (optional), set up abandoned cart recovery.
- **Settings → Languages**: Add English (primary); optionally add other EU languages via LangShop.
- **Settings → Markets**: Create markets for United States, Europe, Canada, Australia; enable currency conversion.

### 3. Theme Setup
- Online Store → Themes → Customize Dawn.
- Upload logo, set colors (match brand identity), configure header/footer.
- Add sections: Hero banner, Featured collection, Product grid, Trust badges, Newsletter.

### 4. Prepare Product Data
- Create a spreadsheet with columns:
  ```
  Handle, Title, Body (HTML), Vendor, Type, Tags, Published, Option1 Name, Option1 Value,
  Variant SKU, Variant Grams, Variant Inventory Tracker, Variant Inventory Qty,
  Variant Inventory Policy, Variant Fulfillment Service, Variant Price,
  Compare At Price, Variant Requires Shipping, Variant Taxable, Variant Barcode,
  Image Src, Image Position, Image Alt Text, Gift Card, SEO Title, SEO Description,
  Google Shopping / MPN, Google Shopping / Age Group, Google Shopping / Gender,
  Variant Image, Variant Weight Unit, Variant Tax Code, Cost per item
  ```
- Fill with data sourced from 1688/Alibaba:
  - Title: English, benefit‑focused (use copywriting skill).
  - Body: HTML description with bullet points, usage instructions, size chart.
  - Images: Download main image + alternate angles; host on Shopify (or external CDN).
  - Variants: Size, color, etc.

### 5. Import Products
- Apps → Import CSV (or use Matrixify for advanced mapping).
- Map columns to Shopify fields.
- Run import → verify a few products.

### 6. Localize Media
- Use image editor (Photoshop, GIMP, or free PhotoPea) to:
  - Remove supplier watermarks.
  - Add lifestyle shots (can source from Unsplash/Pexels or request from supplier).
  - Add badge: “Ships from China – Fast Global Delivery”.
- For videos:
  - Download raw video from supplier.
  - Edit with CapCut: add subtitles (English), trim to 15‑30s, add background music, brand intro/outro.
  - Upload to Shopify product media or host on YouTube and embed.

### 7. Set Up Intelligent Customer Service
- Install **Tidio** app.
- Create FAQ list: Shipping times, Returns policy, Payment safety, Product usage.
- Enable AI Answer Bot (trained on FAQ).
- Add WhatsApp Button (via Tidio or separate widget) for real‑time human support.

### 8. Configure Logistics
- Install **ShipStation** (or **Easyship**) app.
- Connect carrier accounts (DHL, UPS, FedEx, China Post).
- Set shipping rules: Free shipping over $50, flat rate $8, etc.
- Enable real‑time rates at checkout.

### 9. Launch & Promote
- Disable password protection → store live.
- Submit sitemap to Google Search Console.
- Install Facebook & Google channels → sync product catalog for ads.
- Create launch discount code (e.g., WELCOME10) → promote via email/social.

### 10. Ongoing Ops
- Daily: Check orders, fulfill via supplier (dropshipping) or your own warehouse.
- Weekly: Update inventory CSV if supplier provides stock feed.
- Monthly: Review ad performance, A/B test product pages, refresh creatives.

